Iranian students are willing to die for their country’s nuclear program.
They formed a human shield.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around nuclear facilities in Iran.
With their gesture they want to express their support for their country’s nuclear program in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
The students prayed at noon Tuesday before the facility and then chanted death slogans to the United States and Israel.
Several hundred university students formed human shields in the Iranian city of Isfahan on Tuesday around the nuclear technology center in which uranium is being worked.
They seek to demonstrate that they are willing to defend their country’s nuclear program with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), in a recent report, found that Iran, by all indications, is struggling to achieve nuclear weapons.
In Israel there is talk of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
The students prayed at noon at the Isfahan nuclear facilities and then launched death slogans against the U.S. and Israel.
In the event of an attack, which would be to paralyze the Iranian nuclear program, the Isfahan power plant, but also the facilities of Natanz, where uranium is enriched, would be reached, according to Israeli sources.
Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner stuffed
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity at 5%.
Obese children come mostly from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It is again demonstrated what is the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obsessed children feed, for example, on sausages at least twice as often as children from normal weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had had French fries dinner the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence".
In families of overweight children there is no habit of playing sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and almost 900 Basic Education children from all over the Czech Republic participated in the same.
It was already the second edition of the program of "Obesity of is not a coincidence", supported by the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12 thousand children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th year.
A proper diet and enough exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly decrease the number of children who are overweight and even obese.
“Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals daily depending on the regime: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet,” the survey’s results said.
No breakfast but with sausage for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, the details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed hour for breakfast as a family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one eats breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find that in 10% of households nothing is eaten.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children, insane potato chips are consumed much more often.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink sweet soft drinks daily (70%).
As a general rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study made it possible for the chosen children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far removed from the ideal."
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is above all alarming the popularity of sweet soda," the study's final report said.
As the main food, the pasta is taken and the poultry is closely followed.
Practically, children always reject legume and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who filled out the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases a major change in favor of the principles of a healthy diet," the results of the study point out.
It is striking, for example, about sweet soft drinks, where many children would begin to prefer ordinary water.
Children would also more often choose poultry meat and fish for the main food in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
