In Need for Speed: The Run competes across America.
Review
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of carelessness unsuitable from a routine trip during the morning shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but this is of no use, if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, to which the title is added The Run, raised great expectations before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new airs to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as a result, it appears as a game that should not end up being again an action genre without more.
We also feel curious to know how the inserted scenes would look, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be taken for acceptable, but in total counting points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In reality, they cannot be called errors, but rather the incomprehensible reluctance of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
He introduces you to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the West Coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place by a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
That way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the chart is equivalent to that of previous installments in the series.
It is nothing of the other world.
But the desert walk, autumn landscape or high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
Instead, in the mountains you have to be careful not to bury you an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a number of rivals demanded (normal in a classic race), then try to gain time (timed classic duel) and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes the police appear, which does nothing but make things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button just at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you would expect (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer much, but you can’t claim to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race designed with enough action is quite good for this driving style, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, everything in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correctness of driving models, the same is no longer true for collisions.
Games of this type can not be expected to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, when making a very tight overtaking or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or it even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but you can get cranky.
Resets are programmed in such a way that when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game restores you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race only five available resets are available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is nothing more than a help in case something does not go well, but it is not very trusting.
Sometimes, neither reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to the encounter in opposite directions, your opponent overtakes without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed because the "surprise" will always happen before your nose.
The opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always advance you in the same place.
In addition this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at whatever price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to get the vision of the cars that come head-on, so at first you can make the car porridge.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you are sure to be disappointed right away.
And it’s a shame, because even if the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it is often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so that there is no boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during the races.
You have to be attentive to the gasoline pumps next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic supercars for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain roads.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know from the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the upper level, the driver is open to him several possibilities, starting with the car and finishing with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes available other community functions.
One of the hardest elements to understand is how the last race in history is done.
With the car you reach the metro tunnel (pass), where you start running in the dark by the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you the metro convoy and takes you ahead without more.
In the writing we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or if the authors really take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
Well, it is too shame that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and sometimes in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final sensation of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game were to avoid absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game is not finished.
The fun is assured, but prepare because the mistakes will hit you in your eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Students of Velvet".
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During it, twenty choirs from secondary and university centers will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"The Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, on the festival committee is the rector Václav Hampl, "said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the whole festival is the free admission for all audiences to the concert of the high school choirs, which will be held on March 17 at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program is attended by Czech jazz player Karel Růžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Velvet Students" will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, in which university choirs will participate, including the choir of the Carolina University.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choral music at the highest level and promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of the Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will run between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a series of musical events, improvised student shows and morning concerts.
Those interested can find more information on the festival page www.festacademica.cz
