Brand story:
The innovative IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone were to look for a term that would define IBM’s strategy with great precision, the closest would be “long term.”
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and yet a hundred years have passed since its foundation.
The basis of this long-term character was put by the first head of the firm, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He already coined the motto that many problems in the world have a solution if people are willing to think.
His motto "Think!" became his label, around which the life of the future giant will be built (it was also the title of an internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
