They analyze possibility of a count "vote by vote" in Michoacán
According to the data released by the PREP, the difference between first and second place of the election of governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6 thousand 74 total minutes.
The possibility of the count "vote by vote" is a reality in terms of the electoral process this year in Michoacán, where according to the data released by the Preliminary Electoral Results Program (PREP) the difference between first and second place of the election of governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6 thousand 74 total minutes.
In this regard, the president of the General Council of the Electoral Institute of Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, just on November 9, the electoral body approved a series of guidelines in order to harmonize local norms with federal reform in electoral matters.
As will be recalled, Michoacán did not homologate its Political Constitution or its State Electoral Code or its Electoral Justice Law, since the State Congress approved the reforms shortly before the end of the legal deadline for them to enter into force in the present electoral process and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel omitted its publication within the deadlines provided for in the Official State Newspaper Act, arguing that it had some objections.
On November 9, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the local legislature and called the vote of the state president "invalid and illegal" to constitutional reforms, since he has no right to "sanction or veto them".
Interviewed on the possibility of "vote by vote", María de los Ángeles Llanderal explained that thanks to the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of the IEM it will be possible to carry out partial and total counts of the vote by the local electoral body.
In this way, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packages, may occur in the cases that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no act of scrutiny and calculation in the file of the box or not in the possession of the president of the same; or, when there are errors or obvious alterations of the minutes.
In addition, the total count of the vote received in all the boxes of the election may be made when there is an indication that the difference between the alleged candidate winner of the election concerned and the one who obtained the second place in the vote is equal to or less than one percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is the express request of the representative of the party and/or coalition that nominated the second of the candidates indicated.
The total counting of the vote may also be carried out if at the end of the ordinary count it is established that the difference between the candidate allegedly winner and the candidate located in the second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is the express request of the representative of the political party whose candidate came in second, in which case the electoral packages that have been partially counted will be excluded.
It should be mentioned that in this situation is the election of Morelia, where according to the PREP the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, although without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total minutes.
