I think it’s partly because we have nine albums and we can play more than 120 songs and each one likes different songs, so it’s hard to choose which songs to play every night.
When we have two or three songs in the repertoire that we have not played for a while, that keeps us focused and also keeps us surprised because it reminds us of the reasons why we liked those songs and that we could have forgotten.
That makes the show more interesting for us and, therefore, I think it also makes it more interesting for people.
With this tour, they are celebrating 20 years of experience.
Looking back, is it hard to believe everything they have accomplished?
Yeah, absolutely.
First of all, I think none of us imagined we would be in a big rock band and having done it for over 20 years it looked like a dream.
We continue to tell our blessings and are very excited that we can continue to make music together.
We all love each other and we love to create music.
We are fortunate to go to places in the world that we always wanted to go to.
Things couldn't be better for us.
What did it mean to you that you were a fundamental part of the emergence of the grunge?
It has always been an honor to be part of that group of great bands.
We are very close friends with the people of Soundgarden, Mudhoney and Alice in Chains.
It’s amazing when a movement arises from a group of friends and is uncommon.
From time to time, a band from a city emerges, but it is much stranger when five or ten bands leave at the same time from the same city.
We are proud and honored to be part of the Seattle group.
We still play with some of them from time to time.
Last year, we were at a festival with Alice in Chains and were in Canada with Mudhoney, we saw Soundgarden on their tour, so we’re lucky to be friends with them all still and we’re honored to be part of that Seattle sound that came up.
It is also very strange that a band like yours stays united and with the same members for so long.
Yes, four of us are together for 21 years and Matt (Cameron) joined us 13 years ago, which, by itself, is much longer than many bands last.
First, I think we’re all lucky to still be alive and second, we all care about each other.
We are all very close friends and, thanks to that, musical avenues have also been opened that give everyone the freedom to experience.
We trusted each other with each other’s music and it couldn’t be better.
Your relationship with the word fame has not been simple; however, thanks to your success, you have been able to do what you want.
How do you find a balance?
As we have grown, it has been easier to find a balance.
We make sure that not being too touring because it’s easy to fall into that game of the big crowds and people who love your music.
While you remember that people are there for music, that reminds you that you must respect the music and what brought it, without becoming infatuated for being famous and being a rock star, something that none of us really cares about.
How do you remember your other project Mother Love Bone?
I think we wrote very good songs and at first it was a great thing.
We were a band for almost three years and never released an album until after Andy (Andrew Woods) died.
There were a lot of frustrations because it would last so long and the most important thing is that we are still very close friends with Bruce (Fairweather) and Greg (Gilmore), who started in the band with us and when I hear a song or I see a photo I think of the incredible person that Andy was and how it made me laugh, it was always a pleasure to go to work, laugh, talk about music and football and much more.
He was a surprising human being and we missed him.
The national band Las Robertas will be in charge of opening the show in Costa Rica.
Is it true that you know her work, especially Eddie Vedder, and that's why she was picked for the opening?
Yes, the production sent us videos with several proposals and that was the band that we liked the most, so we are eager to see what Las Robertas can offer live and must be very entertaining.
Why do they always change the lyrics of Yellow Ledbetter live?
That's a question for Ed (Eddie Vedder), so I don't know.
He sings it and I think he does it with the first thing he can think of.
As a bassist, what are their influences?
There are so many.
Among the first to come about are Geezer Butler, John Entwistle, C. J. Ramone, John Doe, Paul McCartney, Chuck Dukowski...
There are so many that I could talk all afternoon about the bass players that I love.
How has Pearl Jam managed to keep the grunge relevant despite not being a fashion anymore?
I think all of us always feel a little disconnected from the word grunge.
When I think of her, she reminds me of the bands I mentioned before, like Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all the bands that came up at the same time, and, if there is relevance now, I think it’s a wonderful thing because it’s music worth listening to and bands like Mudhoney are now making better music than ever.
At first, his music had darker content and has now become more positive.
What is the reason for this change?
It’s interesting because I think there are a couple of songs on the new album that may seem lighter, but there are also songs, like The End or Just Breathe that qualify as very dark songs although they may sound a little positive.
With both of them, when Ed touched them, I cried when I heard them and they are deeply dark songs.
I think that when you grow up and there is some trauma in your life and a family member or a friend is lost, those things start to influence your art and your music and those two songs, no doubt, represent that to me.
Also, I think you can be a happy person and still be able to make music that is dark.
Peru:
Fujimori is hospitalized again for medical examinations
Former President Alberto Fujimori was admitted to a public hospital on Tuesday for evaluation for the loss of muscle strength in his legs, his GP reported.
Fujimori, 72, who is serving a 25-year prison sentence for human rights violations committed during his administration (1990-2000), suffers from several ailments, including a cancer in the language for which he has been operated on four times and which is kept under control.
Congressman Alejandro Aguinaga, who is his personal doctor, told Channel N that Fujimori will be evaluated for three days at the National Institute of Neoplastic Diseases to determine the reason for the pain and loss of strength of its lower limbs.
Aguinaga said that in his opinion Fujimori would be a candidate to obtain the benefit of the pardon for humanitarian reasons, however, he said that he does not want it because he is known innocent.
He was operated four times with cancer to the tongue, has a weight loss of 18 kilos to which other pathologies have been combined such as severe erosive gastritis, pancreas cyst, kidney stones, high blood pressure and circulatory problems in the legs, the doctor listed.
Fujimori has been in detention since September 2007 in the National Directorate of Special Operations of the police.
In April 2009 he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the death of 25 people at the hands of an army annihilation squad that operated clandestinely in the early years of his rule.
Mujica travels to Mexico to strengthen political ties
An official delegation, led by the Uruguayan president, José Mujica, and composed of several ministers and businessmen, will begin on Tuesday a visit to Mexico in order to expand trade between the two nations and address political issues in the region.
Mujica will meet next Wednesday with his Mexican counterpart, Felipe Calderón, the highest point of an extensive agenda of meetings with political, commercial authorities and a meeting with the community of Uruguayans residing in Mexico, according to the agenda released by the Uruguayan Presidency.
The meeting between the two presidents, in the city of Guadalajara, will be "propitious for the exchange of information in all that are the political affairs between the two nations," as published by the Presidency of the South American country on its website.
According to local media, Mujica would seek to get Calderón to support Uruguay in the incident with France when French President Nicolas Sarkozy included the South American country in a list of tax havens, at the G20 meeting in the French city of Cannes.
In his speech, Sarkozy threatened to exclude from the international community those countries that remain tax havens, a statement that provoked the rejection of Uruguay and the call for consultation with its ambassador in the European country.
Mexico has been chairing the G20 since November, a group made up of the most powerful emerging and developed countries in the world, and has been in force with the South American country, since January of this year, an agreement to exchange tax information in order to avoid double taxation.
The Uruguayan government has tried in recent years to expedite the realization of fiscal exchange agreements in order to get off the "grey list" of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), formed by countries that did not implement all international standards of tax cooperation.
At the trade level, Mexico and Uruguay have been in force since 2004 a Free Trade Agreement (FTA) that has increased the exchange of goods between the two nations.
The mustached plumber passes the three dimensions with "Super Mario 3D Land"
Super Mario has struggled, tirelessly, over the course of 25 years to save Princess Peach from the clutches of the evil Bowser, but never until now had he done so in three dimensions: in "Super Mario 3D Land" he will fight for the love of the girl in stereoscopic technology.
The title, which arrives this month in stores around the world, has been designed from the beginning to take advantage of the features of the Nintendo 3DS portable console, which allows you to play in three dimensions without using glasses.
"Mario is the character who has to say how stereoscopy should work without glasses," said the head of specialized press of Nintendo in Spain, Omar Álvarez, during the presentation of the video game in Madrid.
Alvarez said "Super Mario 3D Land" is "the first Nintendo video game originally designed for that support", since until now hits such as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" were adaptations of existing titles.
The spokesman for Nintendo has argued that, despite being in 3D, "Super Mario 3D Land" is an "accessible" video game that allows you to enjoy a fast and smooth game.
Alvarez has claimed that "Super Mario 3D Land" contains two games in one: the first part is "simple" to hook less skilled users.
Once overcome, the most experts will be able to take a "second round" to the game levels, which this time present greater difficulty.
In addition, users will be able to choose in real time between an "aggressive D" or one that only affects the depth of the action, but it will be necessary to play in three dimensions to be able to overcome the different challenges and "not succumb to optical illusions".
This foray of Super Mario into the three dimensions also involves the return of the character to a portable console, a fact that did not occur since 2005.
In this video game Nintendo winks to the followers of the saga and repeats the formula of the success of the previous installments, consisting in that the plumber of the mustache will have to travel mine platforms of dangers with the aim of freeing Princess Peach.
Although the player will find new features in the movements, environments, costumes and enemies and also a "playable" Luigi.
Colom endorses Portillo's extradition to the United States
President Álvaro Colom announced on Tuesday that he proceeded with the extradition of former governor Alfonso Portillo to respond in the United States for the conspiracy to launder US$ 70 million.
Thus ends the process for Guatemala to respond to the request of the northern country that claimed Portillo to judge him there.
At a press conference, Colom stated that his decision is due to the independence of judicial and executive powers, taking into account that a court of sentence had already ordered extradition.
He asserted that during his term "he did not put his hands" in judicial decisions and gave process to all the extraditions he has known.
In addition to Portillo, Sergio Ruano Marroquín will be extradited for murder and serious injury, and Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
What Colom did supposes an executive procedure after all the judicial and constitutional instances were exhausted to prosecute the former president from between 2000 and 2004.
According to resolutions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Constitutional Court (CC), Portillo must be extradited once he has resolved his legal status in Guatemala and his human rights are guaranteed.
Portillo was acquitted of the embezzlement of Q120 million in the Ministry of Defense when he was president, which was the process that preceded extradition, but the Public Ministry appealed and reactivated the case.
Trinijove has helped 6,000 young people at risk
The entity was born to avoid the fall in the marginality of children without training
The balance of the first 25 years of life of the social support entity Trinijove is important: 6,000 young people at risk of exclusion have received help to overcome a difficult situation throughout this quarter century.
To this is added the hundred long jobs currently obtained for this social group.
The anniversary served yesterday to take stock at an event held in the former Fabra i Coats factory complex attended by more than 300 people.
Trinijove was born in the neighborhood of Trinitat Vella in 1986 with the aim of helping young people with little training, without work, with problems of dogradiction or in a situation of falling into marginality.
Yesterday’s celebration in Sant Andreu concentrated a large number of officials of entities and institutions that in these 25 years have collaborated with the association.
The varied political representation, in full electoral time, showed the unitary character of the work done by Trinijove.
Together with the president of the Generalitat, Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol, the former Minister of Socialist Education, Ernest Maragall, and the former deputy mayor and current eco-socialist councilor Ricard Gomà attended the event.
Also attending the great hall of the Fabra i Coats were the current councilor of Benestar Social i Família, Josep Lluís Cleries, and the general director of the social work of La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa.
Mas said that Trinijove was born in a very difficult time and that the current one is also, but added that the work done so far "is a good basis".
The president put Trinijove as an example for knowing how to fight against bad circumstances and for giving hope to people with difficulties.
"The crisis is not something new for the entity and for the work it does," he said.
Evicted a squatted estate where macro parties were made
The invaders had taken over 11 of the building’s 13 stories, in Balmes, 51
The 12 occupants left the estate at noon yesterday without offering resistance
Everything seems to indicate that the nightmare that the neighbors of 51 Balmes Street lived has come to an end.
Twelve people voluntarily left the building they occupied illegally yesterday, and where they organized macro parties that despaired the neighborhood, by court order and without the need for police intervention.
When the operation was over, the door lock was changed to prevent a repeat of the situation.
"From now on there will be access control," the administrator said.
The squatters, who had invaded 11 of the 13 floors of the building -the rest are inhabited-, took away the entire electrical installation and part of the water, in addition to painting the walls and leaving waste of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
The first three floors were the scene of the crowded feasts, which lasted up to two days and despaired the tenants.
Next to the building there is a nightclub, Balmes 51, which has also been damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat explained to Europa Press that since the building was occupied the business has fallen by 80%.
The owner of the nightclub points out that the invaders of the farm made unfair competition, since they sold the drinks at three euros, while in the nightclub they are worth 10.
In addition, the owner of the entertainment venue had had to respond to neighborhood complaints of noise, while, according to him, the inconvenience is not caused by the customers of the nightclub, but by the inhabitants of the squat house and, above all, those attending the parties that were organized there, which had increased their frequency and intensity in recent weeks, according to the angry neighbors of the area.
The head of the nightclub explained that the inconvenience was so great that she even reached an agreement with the owner of the property and nine months ago that "forgives" the rent.
The Urban Guard also confirmed that during the last few weeks it had received more complaints from neighbors about the situation.
The president of the municipal group of the PP in the city council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, had claimed last week "to immediately evict the property to end the problems of coexistence and civility that produce the neighbors, as well as the degradation of the area."
The popular leader explained that before the summer there was only one floor of the occupied building, but over the last months the squatters had been entering all the floors of the building and on almost all floors, and that in some even thefts have occurred.
In this sense, he added that, "it is necessary to end impunity and be forceful against the incivism that has been generated in the farm."
Also yesterday, the Mossos evicted a building in Nou Barris.
At 15:30 the police went to 35 Mont-ral Street, after receiving the call from a neighbor who had observed that four people were accessing the building.
All four were arrested at the time.
Park or mountain?
The architects agree on the opportunity of the call beyond controversy about fees
The municipal contest on the 16 doors reopens the debate on the role of Collserola in Barcelona
In the middle of the 80’s, in full swing of the already extinct Metropolitan Corporation of Barcelona (CMB), this Administration printed some promotional pasquins of Collserola.
The brochure defined the mountain as the great park of metropolitan Barcelona.
Moreover, it was accompanied by a comparison, in figures, with the New York Central Park.
With the death of the WBC, in 1987, the park was once again located, in the imagination of many, as the upper limit of Barcelona, being the Catalan capital of the few that do not orient themselves on the north-south axis but above (mountain) -down (sea).
Collserola’s rating as a natural park is in this idea.
The reference was no longer Central Park but Yellowstone, with the wild boars in the role of the Yogi bear.
In these it was until, in September, the city council convened a megacompetition composed of 16 contests for as many access doors to Collserola.
A door refers to the idea of park, no doubt.
Either that or someone pretends to put doors to the field.
The question comes out alone: Collserola, park or mountain?
The contest, both for its purely organizational aspect and for what it supposes of reflection on the city is the topic of conversation among all the Barcelona architects.
It is almost a recurring theme to use when two members of this old caste of elect recognize themselves in an elevator.
And this fact gives rise, precisely, to one of the few coincidences between what three Barcelona architects think, and university professors, who have come forward.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Mòdol and Marta Bayona: the contest is timely.
For Roldán, after addressing the coastal front "it is necessary" to debate "the mountain front", since the speech of Ildefons Cerdà, that of the green apples, has not been carried out.
"It can be started from the basis that the most extensive park in Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things because of its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex", says the architect for whom the title of "doors of Collserola" contains a "lexical trap": we must not think of them "like the accesses to a park, but the delimitation of some areas where you have to act".
Mòdol, as Roldán and Bayonne with experience in the urban world, calls the proposal an "intellectual challenge" with "some dangers".
Dangers derived from how "uncertain it is today to project public space" after the experience lived in the 80's and that had in the area of the Forum "its swan song".
The first fear is the delimitation of a border over where it can be built.
"To limit something is to fix the next step now," that is, its overshoot.
"We must think of new urban planning instruments, because the current ones [in reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)] can lead to real disasters."
More closely at the question, Mòdol believes that, simplifying, the valley slope of Collserola "can be understood as a park, that of Barcelona, not", for a purely topographical issue.
Mòdol recalls that there is already a work done by the Patronat de Collserola that "should not fall flat", although he appreciates the opportunity that the city council offers to its guild to intervene in this project "from the first moment".
And even more, he understands that the proximity of the mountain with the city is the safe conduct that allows architects to enter the debate, but "doubts" about whether it is this technical profile that must lead the multidisciplinary teams ("a success", he points out) that have had to be created: "The architects should be only a tool".
Bayona hints that the answer to the question that gives title to this piece is complex, because in the bases of the contest a global vision of Collserola is missing: "16 transversal contests have been called -he says- in the mountain-sea sense, but there is no longitudinal reading, which sees and understands the area as a whole."
This causes, at least in your case, that you have chosen to participate in the 16 contests.
Otherwise, a project for one of the doors can collide in program and definition with that of the architect of the next door.
In his opinion, however, the city council should ensure that the strip immediately above the Dalt Round should provide, to the fullest extent, for an area of equipment that would make a smooth transition between the city and the green.
Casino forgives Jonah Larrazábal and he will go free
After 72 days of rooting, the legal agent of the Red Casino granted the forgiveness to the brother of the mayor of Monterrey of the process that was followed by alleged blackmail
After 72 days in prison, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal will be released after the legal agent of the Casino Red granted him the pardon before the Second District Penal Court, which follows a process for blackmail against the brother of the mayor of Monterrey.
After the attack on the Casino Royale, the owner of the Red Casino, Sergio Gil García, made public a series of photographs and videos in which Manuel Jonás allegedly demanded the payment of an economic fee for the regional city council to allow the clandestine operation of the bookmaker.
Following the public complaint, the State Attorney General’s Office opened criminal proceedings against the brother of the panista mayor and on September 2 he was arrested and rooted for 30 days.
After four hours before the Agent of the Public Ministry 3 in Heritage Crimes, he was transferred to the House of Arraigo 1, located in the Old Quarter of the state capital.
In that place he remained for the following 49 days when a second arrest warrant was issued after the agent of the Public Prosecutor's Office dismissed the crimes of bribery and organized crime.
On October 19, he was transferred to the Cadereyta prison allegedly for blackmailing the owners of the Red Casino with a million and a half pesos; however, he only stayed for a few hours in the middle-security prison since there were death threats against him.
The authorities allowed him to follow the trial in the municipal cells of San Nicolás de los Garza.
On October 25, he was issued an arrest warrant for the secretary of the Second District Criminal Court, Jorge Yánez, who said that almost two months after inquiries, enough evidence was verified to determine the guilt of Jonás, such as the collection of 1.5 million pesos to the representatives of the bookmaker in exchange for allowing the operation of the same.
On Monday, the legal agent of Casino Red, Víctor Aldo García Gómez, went before the judge José Luis Pecina to request the pardon for the brother of the mayor regio; so in the next few hours he could recover his freedom.
During the legal diligence, the agent of the Public Ministry attached to the Court, Ramiro Arias, questioned García Gómez if the damage had been repaired and who of the partners of the bookmaker was the one who granted the pardon, although the lawyer tried to reserve the name.
Based on file 197/2011, legal pardon is granted to Jonás Larrazábal and no claim may be lodged in the case of the process that was followed; in addition, he will not be required to repair damage or punishment.
After the hearing of the legal agent of the bookmaker, around 15:50 the immediate release of Larrazabal Breton was ordered.
The secretary of the Court, Jorge Yánez, moved to the prison of the municipality of San Nicolás de los Garza to notify Jonás that he has been legally forgiven and his file will be filed.
You will also notify you of the immediate release order issued by the judge.
Secretary Dionisio Pérez Jácome gives details of the plane crash where the Secretary of the Interior, Francisco Blake, and seven other people, lost his life
The Ministry of Communications and Transport (SCT) reported that the results of the accident where the Secretary of the Interior, Francisco Blake Mora, and seven other people, died, indicate that the helicopter was directly impacted on the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot could attempt a hard landing.
During a press conference, Dionisio Pérez Jácome, Secretary of Communications and Transport, mentioned that before taking off the aircraft, the pilot found that the weather conditions were adequate to fly.
"The elements that seem to indicate that the unit had several contacts with the terrain, the blades had contact with trees 25 meters where the unit lost the fuselage."
He also reported that the unit was designed for 19 people, so it had the necessary requirements to transport personnel.
In addition, he said that in the investigations made in the impact area, the appearance of pieces on the ground is not reported.
"In a search they report that there are no parts or components of the ship elsewhere, the impact was presented structurally.
"The design of the helicopter was for 19 passengers, it had adequate requirements to carry passengers.
The terrain presents a slope of seven degrees to 30 degrees of inclination.
At the moment, the secretary assured that it is a priority to have the results before possible; however, the investigation can last several months, it could even reach a year.
For his part, Gilberto López Meyer, general director of Airports and Auxiliary Services, said that at the time of the impact, the helicopter of the Presidential General Staff operated in cruise speed and that this happened in a soft ascending terrain.
"This information strengthens the hypothesis of a normal cruise operation at the time of impact," he said.
At the press conference, the head of the SCT, Pérez Jácome, listed six relevant elements in the investigation:
Visual flight:
According to aeronautical regulations the flight was carried out under the rules of visual flight, this implies that the crew must have visibility during flight and terrain.
Weather conditions:
Reports in the AICM located conditions suitable for takeoff, as the aircraft advances towards the border area between the DF and the State of Mexico, layers of cloud cover were presented at low altitude.
Selected routes:
It is likely that due to the conditions of cloud cover the crew has sought an area of lower elevation and greater visibility towards the valley of Cuernavaca.
Location of impact.
The impact coordinates and the last record of the radar aircraft coincide, probably before the impact there was no loss of control or alteration in the flight path.
Dispersion of aircraft debris in a reduced zone:
The information available so far allows us to assume that the impact occurred on a straight and side path.
The dispersal pattern of the aircraft's remains allows us to assume that the helicopter hit the ground under conditions of structural integrity.
No evidence of fire or explosion has been detected:
Evidence remains at the site of the accident in the wreckage of the ship of some kind of explosion or fire.
The latest research results indicate that he may have had multiple contacts with the terrain.
During the fieldwork, pieces of the aircraft have been found at an elevation of 9 thousand 200 feet above the middle level of the sea, the terrain presents a slope ranging from seven degrees to 30 degrees of inclination.
The photographs show the sequence in which it was predictably dismantled along that path.
The information provides elements that appear to indicate that the helicopter may have had multiple impacts on the ground.
After the thorough search in a wider area than the cordoned-off site, around the accident, no scattered parts of the aircraft have been found, which strengthens the presumption that the impact occurred under conditions of structural integrity.
MSS Announces Protocol to Find Obesity Gene
Social Security leads research to discover the obesity gene in children and young people; it is supported by IPN specialists
The Mexican Institute of Social Security (IMSS) announced that it is directing research to discover the obesity gene in children and young people, called the protocol 'Genetics of childhood and adolescent obesity', which will allow to have markers associated with overweight.
In a statement, the head of the Medical Research Unit in Biochemistry of the Hospital of Specialties of the National Medical Center Siglo XXI, Miguel Cruz López, explained that a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social workers was integrated.
This team is supported by specialists and graduate students from the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Center for Research and Advanced Studies (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
In the research it is invited to participate in the population whether or not they are entitled, to go to the sports units participating in the IMSS in the Valley of Mexico, where the tests are carried out to the minors, every Saturday from 8:00 hours.
He stressed that the protocol began in the Cuauhtémoc Sports Unit (State of Mexico West) and that since October 8, the activity is carried out in the Nezahualcóyolt Sports Unit (State of Mexico Oriente).
Once the goal of gathering 500 or 600 minors is met, the study will continue in the Independence Sports Unit (south of the Federal District) and finally in the Morelos Sports Unit (north of the Federal District).
He explained that the purpose of this research is to know the components and importance of genetics with respect to the development of obesity and to identify in Mexican children and young Mexicans risk factors to prevent the appearance of chronic degenerative diseases.
When World Diabetes Day was celebrated on November 14, he said that the objective is to bring together three thousand children and young people between six and 14 years of age, with the consent and supervision of their parents, for the application of specific questionnaires on food.
They will also be asked about the physical activity and history of diseases, in order to avoid risk factors that trigger conditions such as diabetes or kidney failure.
He explained that on Saturdays anthropometric measurements (weight, height, waist circumference), blood pressure, determination of glucose, triglyceride, cholesterol and insulin levels are applied to all participants (it is sought to identify genes that are associated with childhood obesity).
Cruz López pointed out that this research is due to the concern of health professionals about the alarming weight gain in minors.
"Health surveys in 1999 and 2006 indicated that in just six years there was an increase, in the case of boys, 77 percent in obesity, and girls of 47 percent; in terms of overweight there was also a dramatic increase," said the IMSS specialist.
He indicated that the justification for the search for markers is based on the fact that the population of the country differs from others by their genetic history.
He reported that on average, the Mexican has 65 percent American Indian inheritance, 30 percent European and five percent African and this condition is reflected in the genes that are associated with diabetes and excess weight.
He explained that in general, the genetics of obesity translates into the inability to burn the excess energy we consume (calories) and that is stored in the form of fat.
The researcher explained that the direct benefit for the participants is the comprehensive evaluation of the children, which allows to detect if they have any degree of overweight or obesity.
He even said, the presence of dark-colored folds (acanthosis) in the neck and forearm, which indicate the likelihood of metabolic alterations and even prediabetes.
The information is handled confidentially, doctors deliver it in writing to parents, who are explained each of the measurements and lifestyle changes they must make to prevent disease.
Cruz López explained that there are three main components that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic conditions: sedentary lifestyle, which is the lack of daily physical activity, staying most of the day sitting in front of the television and using means of transport instead of walking short distances.
It is also due to the high caloric intake, that is, the greater consumption of sugary drinks, carbohydrates (tamales, bread, pizza, burger, etc.) with high fat and protein content and the genetics that is analyzed in this protocol.
UNAM asphalt would avoid bumps
Rafael Herrera, a researcher at the Faculty of Chemistry of the UNAM, develops asphalts modified with polymers to produce a blend with better performance, regardless of environmental and temperature conditions
If the signals sent by the pavement were taken care of, it would not be necessary to repair about 200 thousand bumps each rainy season in the Metropolitan Area of the Valley of Mexico, warned Rafael Herrera Nájera, researcher at the Faculty of Chemistry (FQ) of the UNAM, who assured that if the process of construction and maintenance of an asphalt pavement is adequate, the potholes could be reduced in quantity or even eliminated completely.
In his lecture A technological opinion of the potholes, given in the framework of the International Year of Chemistry, announced that the laboratory in charge develops modified asphalts with polymers to produce a mixture with characteristics similar to those of asphalt, but with a greater mechanical resistance, both at high and low temperatures.
Herrera Nájera estimated that this type of modified asphalts could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, such as some cities in the north of the country, to improve their performance and, therefore, the formation of potholes.
He explained that asphalt, the heaviest part of oil, is a set of hydrocarbon molecules, one of high molecular weight, called asphaltenes, and others of low molecular weight, called maltenes, which together give the pavement its characteristic viscoelastic behavior.
The viscoelastic behavior of the asphalt consists in that at high temperatures, about 180 degrees, it behaves like a liquid, at 120 degrees Celsius its viscosity is very high and at 50 degrees Celsius it has an almost solid state, while at very low temperatures, the asphalt becomes brittle, he added.
This means that in the streets the resistance of the asphalt is not uniform, but is modified during the day according to environmental and temperature conditions, warned the chemical engineering specialist.
The FQ researcher observed that the streets of Mexico City are mostly covered by flexible pavement, which is composed of six layers of materials, of which the last three involve the asphalt.
Among the most superficial layers is the asphalt folder, made up of small stones bathed in asphalt and then compacted.
Each of the stones that constitutes the folder, she said, is bathed with asphalt.
When the vehicles are transited and efforts are generated, it allows the forces to spread very well on the pavement.
If it were modified asphalt they would diffuse even better, the chemical engineer said.
On the asphalt folder, he abounded, a last layer is placed called a rolling folder, which is made of a fine stone material, that is, a sand that is also bathed in asphalt.
Since it is the layer that will be in contact with the tires of the vehicles, it must have more mechanical force than the asphalt folder and provide friction on the road.
Being the part of the pavement that will receive and diffuse the efforts, the rolling folder also requires having the appropriate thickness and the material from which it is made must be taken care of.
Climate, especially humidity and temperature variations, are also a very important factor to consider, especially water, he said, because it considerably affects the performance of the asphalt folder.
When the ground is moistened, the water diffuses into the folder and it is difficult for it to come out, this causes a softening of all the layers of the pavement and, therefore, the formation of potholes.
In the process of forming a pothole, he said, the first to wear out is the bearing film and only then the asphalt folder is affected, but the damage does not occur instantly, but is a process that should be addressed to the first signals with adequate maintenance programs.
The also member of the National System of Researchers explained that the vehicle load is another important factor in the formation of potholes and, therefore, the thickness of each of the layers of the pavement must always be in relation to the vehicle load and ensure that it is fulfilled, to avoid that potholes are formed frequently.
Rafael Herrera warned that there is still much to investigate and work on asphalt, for example, asphalt emulsions, which in other countries are already even on the market and allow to repair potholes easily and without the need to use high temperatures.
