However, according to experts, who have also studied the situation in all countries where such practices have been legalized or do not constitute a criminal offence, there is no evidence that the fact that they are not considered a criminal offence has not caused an abuse of its application, i.e. the use of euthanasia or assisted suicide with non-competent persons or who have not consented.
